1
00:00:03,330 --> 00:00:06,800
(The First "I'm Sorry, I Love You" Special)

2
00:00:07,820 --> 00:00:09,000
(A special project for the 300th episode.)

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,050
- "I'm sorry"?
 -  I'm sorry.

4
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,000
(Some guests had a bad experience on Running Man.)

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,800
- I'm sorry.
 -  I'm sorry.

6
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,860
- I want to apologise to you.
 -  Please accept our apology.

7
00:00:15,860 --> 00:00:17,700
(Running Man will apologise today.)

8
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:19,530
- You're so pretty.
 -  That's too much.

9
00:00:19,530 --> 00:00:20,910
This is too hard.

10
00:00:20,910 --> 00:00:22,520
(They are customised apologies.)

11
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:23,640
You jerk.

12
00:00:25,340 --> 00:00:28,460
(Will the apologies be accepted?)

13
00:00:28,460 --> 00:00:29,470
Don't hold him.

14
00:00:29,940 --> 00:00:32,270
(They confess the truth for the first time in six years.)

15
00:00:32,270 --> 00:00:36,940
I wasn't healthy, so I was put in a slump.

16
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:43,140
I thought I should leave Running Man at this point.

17
00:00:44,870 --> 00:00:46,030
Thank you.

18
00:00:46,030 --> 00:00:48,210
(The Running Man stories will now unfold.)

19
00:00:50,870 --> 00:00:53,070
(It's 8am on the day of filming.)

20
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:58,110
(Jae Seok begins the day with a cup of tea.)

21
00:01:03,870 --> 00:01:05,410
(Seok Jin's nose is swollen.)

22
00:01:06,590 --> 00:01:07,670
Shall we go?

23
00:01:07,670 --> 00:01:08,940
(Ji Hyo woke up early today.)

24
00:01:08,940 --> 00:01:10,680
(Let's go)

25
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:13,780
- Are we leaving now?
 -  Yes.

26
00:01:15,420 --> 00:01:18,520
(This is how the Running Man members begin their commute.)

27
00:01:21,180 --> 00:01:22,750
The weather is nice.

28
00:01:24,150 --> 00:01:25,340
It's a lovely day.

29
00:01:25,340 --> 00:01:27,510
(Enjoying the spring day, they turn on the radio.)

30
00:01:27,510 --> 00:01:30,810
You're listening to "Beautiful Morning" and I'm Kim Chang Wan.

31
00:01:30,810 --> 00:01:33,880
You must be caught in traffic and feeling tired right now.

32
00:01:34,220 --> 00:01:38,520
I have a letter that will wake you up.

33
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:41,810
It's a letter from Jee Seok Jin who lives in Bundang-gu...

34
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:44,820
to Lee Kwang Soo who lives in Geumho-dong.

35
00:01:45,850 --> 00:01:47,720
"Dearest Kwang Soo."

36
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:50,550
- "This is Seok Jin."
 -  Is this from Seok Jin?

37
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:55,620
"Do you remember? While we were filming,"

38
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:58,310
"I told you that no matter how hard you try,"

39
00:01:58,310 --> 00:02:00,520
"you'll only be as handsome as Song Joong Ki's feet."

40
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,620
"I'm so sorry."

41
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:07,730
"I never expected the staff would put a foot on your face."

42
00:02:07,730 --> 00:02:11,920
"You're the Prince of Asia. I just wanted to be funny."

43
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,490
It was funny.

44
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,320
"Let's continue to work hard."

45
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:19,620
"I hope we'll all be happy. From Seok Jin."

46
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:23,800
Let's listen to a song that speaks Seok Jin's mind.

47
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,250
"A Foot" by Shin Il Soo.

48
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:27,850
(Laughing)

49
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:31,650
Is there a song called "A Foot"? Seriously?

50
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:33,520
What does a foot have to do with me?

51
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:40,140
This is the happiest foot in the world

52
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:43,490
I'll read the next letter.

53
00:02:43,490 --> 00:02:47,650
It's a letter from Haha who lives in Mapo-gu.

54
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:51,980
"Dear Gary. It all started last winter."

55
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:55,950
"While we were playing a game in the X-Man Special,"

56
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:59,410
"I asked you if you're a squid."

57
00:02:59,410 --> 00:03:02,660
"Everyone burst into laughter at my joke."

58
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:06,050
"It's been a few months and everybody calls you a squid now."

59
00:03:06,980 --> 00:03:10,310
(Who are you to call me a squid?)

60
00:03:10,310 --> 00:03:11,420
Did you see it?

61
00:03:13,550 --> 00:03:15,410
(Giggling)

62
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:17,620
(What is it?)

63
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,510
He is the real squid.

64
00:03:20,510 --> 00:03:22,280
(Meet the squid's friend.)

65
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,250
(It's hard to decide which of the two is uglier.)

66
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:29,630
Let me read you the last letter.

67
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:33,650
It's from Kwang Soo, the youngest member of Running Man.

68
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:36,070
"Dear Haha."

69
00:03:36,070 --> 00:03:40,520
"Do you know what my favourite part of our team dinner is?"

70
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,820
"It's when we switch roles and I get to be older than you."

71
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:48,080
"One day, you said I only have three more chances to do that."

72
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:50,740
"I've already used all my chances."

73
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:53,010
"I wasn't able to restrain myself and I used them all."

74
00:03:53,010 --> 00:03:55,330
"It's only April."

75
00:03:55,330 --> 00:03:58,420
"I can't wait to treat you as if you're younger than me."

76
00:03:58,420 --> 00:04:02,010
"I promise I won't waste more chances. I'll see you soon."

77
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:05,310
- "I'm sorry I treat you like..."
 -  Chang Wan's voice...

78
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:08,620
makes the stories sound so beautiful.

79
00:04:08,620 --> 00:04:11,310
They're not supposed to be beautiful.

80
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:13,870
"See you in a bit, smiling. I love you."

81
00:04:13,870 --> 00:04:19,920
I'm touched by the friendship between the Running Man members.

82
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:23,070
I hope this warmed your hearts on the way to the set.

83
00:04:23,070 --> 00:04:26,780
I'll always cheer for Running Man.

84
00:04:26,780 --> 00:04:30,180
You've listened to "Beautiful Morning" and I am Kim Chang Wan.

85
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:33,320
I love Chang Wan's voice.

86
00:04:34,620 --> 00:04:35,780
This was nice.

87
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:38,450
(What will be waiting for them today?)

88
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:40,570
(The members arrive at SBS.)

89
00:04:40,570 --> 00:04:43,110
Did you listen to the radio on the way here?

90
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:45,440
- Yes.
 -  It was embarrassing.

91
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:49,050
I can't look at the person I wrote to in the eye.

92
00:04:49,550 --> 00:04:52,660
- It is a bit embarrassing.
 -  It is.

93
00:04:52,660 --> 00:04:54,800
Haha, will you give Kwang Soo more chances?

94
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,740
- I already gave him enough.
 -  Wasn't it more than 10?

95
00:04:57,740 --> 00:04:59,410
- He doesn't need my permission.
 -  It's a free pass for him.

96
00:04:59,410 --> 00:05:00,850
I can even do it now. Hey!

97
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,470
- Also...
 -  You guys are funny.

98
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:05,740
- Continue to talk like that.
 -  You should...

99
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:08,170
pay him for more chances.

100
00:05:08,170 --> 00:05:11,950
- You should pay him.
 -  I accept credit cards.

101
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:14,380
- Today's theme is...
 -  Yes.

102
00:05:15,290 --> 00:05:16,920
Today's theme is this.

103
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,240
Something's coming down.

104
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,140
(It's a spring special.)

105
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:22,620
Today's theme is this.

106
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:25,720
- "I'm sorry?"
 -  "I'm sorry."

107
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:31,450
Today, we'll shoot the First "I'm Sorry, I Love You" Special.

108
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:34,090
If there's anyone among our guests...

109
00:05:34,090 --> 00:05:37,840
that you feel sorry to or wish to make things better with,

110
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:41,540
you'll go apologise to them and do them a favour.

111
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:43,720
(The members will provide a special apology service.)

112
00:05:44,380 --> 00:05:48,150
Among our guests, I feel sorry for Kwang Soo.

113
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,240
- Why?
 -  Why am I a guest?

114
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,270
- Aren't you a guest?
 -  What are you talking about?

115
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:55,930
- You've been a guest for six years.
 -  Shouldn't I be accepted by now?

116
00:05:55,930 --> 00:05:58,540
- He's been with us for six years.
 -  That's why I'm sorry.

117
00:05:58,540 --> 00:06:00,840
He always manages to match his clothes with us.

118
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:01,920
Do you think I prepared these clothes?

119
00:06:02,650 --> 00:06:04,540
Do you think I bought them myself?

120
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:07,050
You kept coming back for six years.

121
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,540
That's absurd.

122
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:11,070
You were our first guest and you came every week.

123
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:13,140
- We couldn't kick you out.
 -  I'm a member.

124
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:14,780
We're so kind.

125
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:17,720
(I'm Sorry, I Love You)

126
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:20,940
(The members visit the guests they feel sorry to.)

127
00:06:20,940 --> 00:06:23,020
There's someone I feel sorry to.

128
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:24,950
(Feelings of regret begin to form.)

129
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:28,590
- Haeryung from BESTie.
 -  Exactly. Haeryung.

130
00:06:28,590 --> 00:06:31,940
- I failed to lift her on my back.
 -  I remember.

131
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:33,770
- That's right.
 -  I didn't succeed.

132
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:36,010
- Haeryung.
 -  That's right.

133
00:06:36,010 --> 00:06:38,650
- I feel most sorry to her.
 -  I see.

134
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:41,240
I feel so sorry to G-Dragon as well.

135
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,340
- G-Dragon.
 -  Do you remember?

136
00:06:43,340 --> 00:06:47,290
- I felt sorry, too.
 -  He seemed dispirited later on.

137
00:06:47,290 --> 00:06:50,000
- We should feel sorry for him.
 -  Really.

138
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,980
G-Dragon was going through a hard time back then.

139
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:54,280
He was having a hard time.

140
00:06:56,580 --> 00:07:01,640
(Spring flowers are in full bloom in the streets of Samcheong-dong.)

141
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:06,620
(Today's first guest is shooting a commercial.)

142
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:11,380
(He's dazzling like the spring weather.)

143
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:18,150
(It's the popular actor, Park Seo Joon.)

144
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:21,070
Tell me how the driver is doing!

145
00:07:21,070 --> 00:07:22,450
(He's stolen many hearts with his acting.)

146
00:07:22,450 --> 00:07:23,820
You're so cute.

147
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:26,130
- How are you feeling?
 -  This is so nice.

148
00:07:26,130 --> 00:07:27,970
(Through his four appearances on Running Man,)

149
00:07:27,970 --> 00:07:30,020
(he has proven himself as an entertainer.)

150
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:31,610
You don't look like yourself.

151
00:07:31,610 --> 00:07:33,480
You're still handsome.

152
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:36,570
- Everybody, Seo Joon is here.
 -  Seo Joon!

153
00:07:36,570 --> 00:07:38,010
- I'm sorry!
 -  Seo Joon, we're sorry!

154
00:07:38,010 --> 00:07:40,310
- Seo Joon, I'm sorry!
 -  Seo Joon, I'm sorry.

155
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:42,640
- It's Park Seo Joon!
 -  What are you sorry for?

156
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,770
(Why are they apologising to Seo Joon?)

157
00:07:43,770 --> 00:07:45,710
- I'm sorry, Seo Joon.
 -  It's good to see you.

158
00:07:45,710 --> 00:07:47,640
- I'm sorry.
 -  You look so handsome.

159
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:50,710
You're so handsome. Why are you so handsome?

160
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:54,340
He actually has the best type of face.

161
00:07:54,340 --> 00:07:56,810
- You'll never get sick of him.
 -  No, you won't.

162
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:58,810
- He only becomes more charming.
 -  By the way,

163
00:07:58,810 --> 00:08:01,340
you've only met Seo Joon as a guest on the show.

164
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:03,210
But I've watched him film in other places.

165
00:08:03,210 --> 00:08:05,310
- He's a big star.
 -  Wasn't he handsome?

166
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:07,910
There were these huge umbrellas covering him the whole time.

167
00:08:07,910 --> 00:08:10,210
- That's amazing.
 -  We're sorry.

168
00:08:10,210 --> 00:08:12,270
- We have to hold it ourselves.
 -  Does anybody have an umbrella?

169
00:08:12,270 --> 00:08:14,640
- He's going to get sunburned.
 -  Seo Joon.

170
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,370
- Seo Joon, we're sorry.
 -  Why are you...

171
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:18,220
treating me nicer than usual?

172
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,970
(They're suddenly treating him nicely.)

173
00:08:21,970 --> 00:08:25,070
Make sure his face doesn't get covered by the shade.

174
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:27,220
- It's covering his face already.
 -  I'm sorry, Seo Joon.

175
00:08:27,780 --> 00:08:29,310
- Seo Joon!
 -  Thank you.

176
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:31,390
We should have done this for you earlier.

177
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,570
Let me hold this for you. I have so much energy left over.

178
00:08:34,570 --> 00:08:35,890
He has a lot of energy remaining.

179
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:40,470
This is Seo Joon's fifth appearance on our show.

180
00:08:40,470 --> 00:08:41,840
- Already?
 -  Really?

181
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:44,610
- He's appeared a lot on this show.
 -  No kidding.

182
00:08:44,610 --> 00:08:47,510
And every time he was on it, he always worked hard.

183
00:08:47,510 --> 00:08:50,270
I'm pretty sure you all know already,

184
00:08:50,270 --> 00:08:52,890
- but let me read this for you.
 -  Go ahead.

185
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,890
"Park Seo Joon is like family to Running Man."

186
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,040
Isn't that just our opinion?

187
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:01,570
"During the winter, we made you walk..."

188
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:03,750
"barefoot in the icy water."

189
00:09:04,350 --> 00:09:07,770
"And even worse, during the Beautiful Youth Race,"

190
00:09:07,770 --> 00:09:11,040
"your name was mistakenly written as Lee Seo Joon."

191
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:12,170
"We sincerely apologise."

192
00:09:12,170 --> 00:09:13,640
- He deserves an apology.
 -  We were wrong.

193
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:16,140
That's like saying Park Jae Seok instead of Yu Jae Seok.

194
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:18,070
- That was bad.
 -  We must apologise.

195
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:21,410
Seo Joon, we're really sorry for the mistake with the captions.

196
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:24,470
Mistakes like that happen.

197
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:27,740
I was okay with it, but my parents...

198
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:29,050
(My parents were hurt.)

199
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:30,840
That's even more hurtful.

200
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:33,580
You changed my father's last name to "Lee".

201
00:09:34,020 --> 00:09:36,470
- You guys should know better.
 -  You hurt his family.

202
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:39,620
- Let's toss him in the air, then.
 -  All right.

203
00:09:40,350 --> 00:09:41,570
- What?
 -  All of a sudden?

204
00:09:41,570 --> 00:09:42,970
- Seo Joon.
 -  No, we owe you this much.

205
00:09:42,970 --> 00:09:44,880
- Come here, Seo Joon.
 -  Come here.

206
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,940
- We have to do this for you.
 -  Don't worry.

207
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:48,780
(This is the best way to apologise.)

208
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,420
- In 1, 2, 3.
 -  In 1, 2, 3.

209
00:09:51,150 --> 00:09:52,450
- In 1, 2, 3.
 -  In 1, 2, 3.

210
00:09:52,450 --> 00:09:53,940
- One more time.
 -  In 1, 2, 3.

211
00:09:53,940 --> 00:09:55,240
(This looks like a World Cup celebration.)

212
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,240
- Be careful.
 -  That was good.

213
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,140
- That came out of nowhere.
 -  No, it's because...

214
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:01,010
I don't know if this is enough to receive forgiveness.

215
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:03,740
Seo Joon got frostbitten last time.

216
00:10:03,740 --> 00:10:06,950
I was in the middle of shooting a drama at the time.

217
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:10,300
I ended up with a bad flu the next day.

218
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,470
It was cold that day.

219
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:13,710
We walked barefoot for that episode.

220
00:10:13,710 --> 00:10:16,570
The ground was covered in snow and we walked on it with bare feet.

221
00:10:16,570 --> 00:10:18,710
- It wasn't even for a short time.
 -  Exactly.

222
00:10:18,710 --> 00:10:20,770
It was very cold but Seo Joon acted like he was fine.

223
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:22,410
Why did you do that?

224
00:10:22,410 --> 00:10:24,940
- Because it was my first time.
 -  It was his first time on the show.

225
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:26,510
- He wanted to try his best.
 -  I wanted to do my best.

226
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:27,840
- That's why.
 -  You're the best.

227
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:31,740
It was freezing, right? He kept on saying he wasn't cold.

228
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:35,710
- Let's take care of his feet today.
 -  Let's wipe them for him.

229
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:36,770
- Let's do it together.
 -  I hope it's not too late.

230
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:39,750
- Let's wash his feet.
 -  All right.

231
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,220
Let's get ready.

232
00:10:41,220 --> 00:10:42,840
- Seriously?
 -  Come on over.

233
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,170
- Come here.
 -  Don't feel troubled, Seo Joon.

234
00:10:45,170 --> 00:10:47,110
We thought about bathing you, too.

235
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:49,240
- This doesn't look right.
 -  Have a seat.

236
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:50,840
- Have a seat.
 -  Sit down, Seo Joon.

237
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,910
This is a full set.

238
00:10:52,910 --> 00:10:55,920
- Seo Joon, take off your shoes.
 -  Take them off.

239
00:10:56,450 --> 00:10:57,840
I'm sorry, Seo Joon.

240
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,870
- I didn't know.
 -  I'm wearing socks.

