1223
00:48:04,110 --> 00:48:06,650
- Thank you, Mrs Moon.
 -  Take care!

1224
00:48:07,320 --> 00:48:10,040
I'll take charge and give you some training tips.

1225
00:48:10,040 --> 00:48:11,350
It turned out well in the end.

1226
00:48:11,750 --> 00:48:13,270
- What's that?
 -  It's a gift.

1227
00:48:13,270 --> 00:48:14,340
I didn't know there was a gift.

1228
00:48:14,340 --> 00:48:15,760
- What's this?
 -  Are you going to mock him?

1229
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:17,310
- They look like pyjamas.
 -  Let's open this first.

1230
00:48:17,310 --> 00:48:18,470
- This one first?
 -  Yes.

1231
00:48:18,470 --> 00:48:19,710
(What's the first gift?)

1232
00:48:19,710 --> 00:48:20,930
- What's that?
 -  What is it?

1233
00:48:20,930 --> 00:48:22,770
- I have a bad feeling about this.
 -  It's a shirt.

1234
00:48:22,770 --> 00:48:26,380
- It's a t-shirt with a design.
 -  There are muscles on it.

1235
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:29,120
- Why?
 -  What is it?

1236
00:48:30,950 --> 00:48:32,070
I have muscles.

1237
00:48:32,070 --> 00:48:33,340
(It's a t-shirt with a muscular body on it.)

1238
00:48:33,340 --> 00:48:34,880
- Goodness.
 -  This is even sadder.

1239
00:48:36,020 --> 00:48:37,870
I don't think it'll fit you.

1240
00:48:37,870 --> 00:48:39,950
(He manages to put his head through.)

1241
00:48:41,050 --> 00:48:43,580
- That's not how you do it.
 -  This is small.

1242
00:48:45,820 --> 00:48:46,880
It fits.

1243
00:48:47,220 --> 00:48:48,630
- It fits you.
 -  It does fit.

1244
00:48:48,630 --> 00:48:51,270
It fits well on top of your shirt.

1245
00:48:51,270 --> 00:48:53,180
Do you agree, Kwang Soo?

1246
00:48:53,620 --> 00:48:55,240
- I can't even breathe.
 -  Well, I mean...

1247
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:57,020
- Does it have a hood?
 -  You need to take it out.

1248
00:48:57,450 --> 00:49:00,370
Can you take a picture of it and post it up on SNS?

1249
00:49:00,370 --> 00:49:02,640
- Post it up for him.
 -  Sure, I will.

1250
00:49:02,640 --> 00:49:04,150
Can someone take a picture for us?

1251
00:49:04,780 --> 00:49:06,980
In 1, 2, 3.

1252
00:49:07,820 --> 00:49:10,850
(Hee Jun is not a fatty.)

1253
00:49:11,220 --> 00:49:12,650
- We're sorry.
 -  All right, Hee Jun.

1254
00:49:13,120 --> 00:49:15,400
- Please accept our apology.
 -  Okay.

1255
00:49:15,400 --> 00:49:16,420
Thanks so much.

1256
00:49:16,750 --> 00:49:18,220
- Hee Jun.
 -  Take an apple...

1257
00:49:18,220 --> 00:49:20,340
You must take a bite of an apple to accept our apology.

1258
00:49:20,340 --> 00:49:21,570
- Is that so?
 -  Yes.

1259
00:49:21,570 --> 00:49:22,920
I'm rooting for you, Hee Jun.

1260
00:49:24,280 --> 00:49:25,920
(Taking a bite)

1261
00:49:26,650 --> 00:49:28,110
It's delicious.

1262
00:49:28,110 --> 00:49:29,520
He accepted the apology.

1263
00:49:29,520 --> 00:49:31,640
I'm seriously rooting for you.

1264
00:49:31,640 --> 00:49:32,650
(Hee Jun accepts their apology.)

1265
00:49:33,450 --> 00:49:35,480
(I'm Sorry, I Love You)

1266
00:49:36,280 --> 00:49:37,370
(They're going to meet the last guest.)

1267
00:49:37,370 --> 00:49:38,520
Who are we apologising to?

1268
00:49:39,320 --> 00:49:41,310
- I'm not sure.
 -  Who could it be?

1269
00:49:41,310 --> 00:49:43,150
(Who could be the last guest?)

1270
00:49:45,380 --> 00:49:46,380
Who could it be?

1271
00:49:47,250 --> 00:49:48,420
Thank you for the ride.

1272
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:52,310
(They have reached the end of a long day.)

1273
00:49:52,310 --> 00:49:54,920
You have all worked hard to serve the guests.

1274
00:49:54,920 --> 00:49:58,170
The last Apology Service is the most important one.

1275
00:49:58,170 --> 00:49:59,220
It's time...

1276
00:49:59,650 --> 00:50:01,820
for an Apology Service amongst the members.

1277
00:50:02,220 --> 00:50:04,820
(It's an Apology Service amongst Running Man members.)

1278
00:50:05,320 --> 00:50:06,440
No way.

1279
00:50:06,440 --> 00:50:08,240
I'm cringing already.

1280
00:50:08,240 --> 00:50:10,080
This is quite awkward.

1281
00:50:10,480 --> 00:50:12,840
In case you don't know what to say, write it down first.

1282
00:50:12,840 --> 00:50:15,110
Can't we just talk amongst ourselves?

1283
00:50:15,110 --> 00:50:16,480
- What are we doing?
 -  We'll talk amongst ourselves.

1284
00:50:17,750 --> 00:50:19,510
(They can't help but laugh.)

1285
00:50:19,510 --> 00:50:20,650
What am I sorry about?

1286
00:50:21,450 --> 00:50:22,720
I've never thought about this.

1287
00:50:23,820 --> 00:50:24,920
Do I just write anything?

1288
00:50:26,580 --> 00:50:29,080
(It's the first time they're writing to each other in six years.)

1289
00:50:30,250 --> 00:50:31,540
(They meet every week.)

1290
00:50:31,540 --> 00:50:32,610
I finished.

1291
00:50:32,610 --> 00:50:33,910
(Would they have anything to say?)

1292
00:50:33,910 --> 00:50:35,520
- Are you done?
 -  Yes.

1293
00:50:36,550 --> 00:50:42,720
(They slowly fill the pages with their words.)

1294
00:50:44,720 --> 00:50:45,810
I don't know what to write.

1295
00:50:45,810 --> 00:50:51,650
(Among them, Jae Seok has a difficult time writing.)

1296
00:50:54,750 --> 00:50:59,630
(He doesn't know how to condense his feelings onto a single page...)

1297
00:50:59,630 --> 00:51:04,480
(for the 6 members who spent the past 6 years with him.)

1298
00:51:05,950 --> 00:51:11,080
(Gathering courage, he picks up the pen and begins to write.)

1299
00:51:16,550 --> 00:51:19,910
Jae Seok, you can go into the white room.

1300
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:20,920
- Me?
 -  Yes.

1301
00:51:21,650 --> 00:51:23,810
Kwang Soo, you can head to the recreational vehicle.

1302
00:51:23,810 --> 00:51:26,840
(Kwang Soo will share a conversation with someone there.)

1303
00:51:26,840 --> 00:51:27,980
- Seok Jin.
 -  Yes.

1304
00:51:28,880 --> 00:51:30,370
- Go to the food stand.
 -  The food stand?

1305
00:51:30,370 --> 00:51:31,710
Okay. I don't even drink.

1306
00:51:31,710 --> 00:51:33,380
(Seok Jin heads to the food stand.)

1307
00:51:33,980 --> 00:51:35,550
(These spaces are perfect for two people.)

1308
00:51:36,780 --> 00:51:39,610
(Jae Seok enters a white room.)

1309
00:51:39,610 --> 00:51:43,050
(Who will join him?)

1310
00:51:47,280 --> 00:51:48,480
(I knew it was going to be you.)

1311
00:51:49,150 --> 00:51:51,080
- I knew it was going to be you.
 -  What is this?

1312
00:51:51,780 --> 00:51:53,650
- Why...
 -  Gosh.

1313
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:56,210
- What is this, anyway?
 -  I don't know.

1314
00:51:56,210 --> 00:51:58,470
- Why do we have to do this?
 -  I have no idea.

1315
00:51:58,470 --> 00:52:00,270
(This is so awkward.)

1316
00:52:00,270 --> 00:52:02,010
- Goodness.
 -  What? Why?

1317
00:52:02,010 --> 00:52:03,810
- Did you write to me?
 -  No.

1318
00:52:03,810 --> 00:52:05,380
- Me neither.
 -  Gosh.

1319
00:52:05,980 --> 00:52:07,300
- Seriously.
 -  Goodness.

1320
00:52:07,300 --> 00:52:08,350
So...

1321
00:52:09,020 --> 00:52:11,720
- I don't know what this is about.
 -  Well...

1322
00:52:12,550 --> 00:52:16,040
Why do we have to face each other? It's awkward.

1323
00:52:16,040 --> 00:52:18,470
Exactly. Oh, dear.

1324
00:52:18,470 --> 00:52:20,830
I never thought it was awkward between us before.

1325
00:52:20,830 --> 00:52:22,540
- This makes us awkward.
 -  It does.

1326
00:52:22,540 --> 00:52:24,040
What's this about?

1327
00:52:24,040 --> 00:52:27,650
- It's awkward like this.
 -  Exactly.

1328
00:52:28,350 --> 00:52:30,240
I don't know what we are supposed to talk about.

1329
00:52:30,240 --> 00:52:32,910
I didn't write anything special.

1330
00:52:32,910 --> 00:52:37,630
I just wrote this. It must be the same for the rest of us,

1331
00:52:37,630 --> 00:52:40,750
but since we have different roles on this show,

1332
00:52:41,520 --> 00:52:42,720
sometimes...

1333
00:52:43,420 --> 00:52:46,970
I end up acting aggressively.

1334
00:52:46,970 --> 00:52:48,510
- But I had to because...
 -  Of course.

1335
00:52:48,510 --> 00:52:50,110
- everybody is so nice.
 -  Right. We know...

1336
00:52:50,110 --> 00:52:53,710
that you have to take on a certain role in playing the villain.

1337
00:52:53,710 --> 00:52:55,050
Exactly. So even when I talk,

1338
00:52:55,380 --> 00:52:57,420
I speak aggressively.

1339
00:52:58,750 --> 00:53:00,150
- I get it.
 -  Gosh.

1340
00:53:00,620 --> 00:53:03,770
Sometimes, I know I've gone too far but I still say those words.

1341
00:53:03,770 --> 00:53:05,880
- Right.
 -  I say them on purpose.

1342
00:53:06,250 --> 00:53:07,770
This is part of the show.

1343
00:53:07,770 --> 00:53:10,210
- Of course.
 -  Since it's part of the show,

1344
00:53:10,210 --> 00:53:13,110
- I think that you'll understand me.
 -  Certainly.

1345
00:53:13,110 --> 00:53:15,150
But still, I sometimes...

1346
00:53:15,480 --> 00:53:20,850
think you and Seok Jin might be offended by what I do.

1347
00:53:20,850 --> 00:53:25,160
But for our show, we have to get physical so it can turn violent.

1348
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:26,550
That's understandable.

1349
00:53:27,280 --> 00:53:28,880
I mentioned this before,

1350
00:53:29,850 --> 00:53:31,620
but athletes reach their prime as well.

1351
00:53:31,950 --> 00:53:33,550
- You know what I mean, right?
 -  I know.

1352
00:53:33,880 --> 00:53:35,750
Since my body is starting to ache,

1353
00:53:36,750 --> 00:53:41,250
there are more things I can't do on Running Man.

1354
00:53:42,120 --> 00:53:44,250
That's when I was in a slump.

1355
00:53:44,750 --> 00:53:46,080
It was because...

1356
00:53:47,420 --> 00:53:49,900
I knew people had expectations for me.

1357
00:53:49,900 --> 00:53:52,250
But my body wouldn't heal.

1358
00:53:52,920 --> 00:53:55,980
So I couldn't fulfil my role in those moments.

1359
00:53:56,420 --> 00:53:58,220
I was put down every time that happened.

1360
00:53:59,180 --> 00:54:02,210
There were times when I questioned...

1361
00:54:02,210 --> 00:54:04,650
- my place on this show.
 -  Right.

1362
00:54:05,550 --> 00:54:07,110
But I knew that if I gave this up,

1363
00:54:07,110 --> 00:54:10,950
I wouldn't be invited to appear on other programmes.

1364
00:54:11,650 --> 00:54:14,720
So there was a time when I struggled with the thought.

1365
00:54:14,720 --> 00:54:16,210
(Jong Kook expresses his anxiety for the first time.)

1366
00:54:16,210 --> 00:54:18,480
- I know.
 -  Because of that, when I spoke,

1367
00:54:18,950 --> 00:54:22,650
I was being aggressive to cover up my flaws.

1368
00:54:22,650 --> 00:54:24,620
- I see.
 -  That's what I turned to.

1369
00:54:25,150 --> 00:54:31,620
But I think that could have been too much for the members and guests.

1370
00:54:32,720 --> 00:54:36,050
(Jae Seok quietly listens to Jong Kook.)

1371
00:54:37,550 --> 00:54:40,540
(Meanwhile, Kwang Soo is waiting inside the van.)

1372
00:54:40,540 --> 00:54:43,110
(Someone is here.)

1373
00:54:43,110 --> 00:54:45,050
(Laughing)

1374
00:54:46,020 --> 00:54:48,770
(He bursts into laughter...)

1375
00:54:48,770 --> 00:54:52,240
(as soon as he sees Ji Hyo.)

1376
00:54:52,240 --> 00:54:53,470
This is insane.

1377
00:54:53,470 --> 00:54:55,840
This is so awkward, Kwang Soo.

1378
00:54:55,840 --> 00:54:57,020
(This is so awkward, Kwang Soo.)

1379
00:54:57,980 --> 00:54:59,270
Oh goodness.

1380
00:54:59,270 --> 00:55:00,740
(His face has turned red in embarrassment.)

1381
00:55:00,740 --> 00:55:02,380
What is this for?

1382
00:55:02,750 --> 00:55:05,350
Why are you making us do this?

1383
00:55:06,420 --> 00:55:07,820
What are we supposed to do here?

1384
00:55:08,950 --> 00:55:10,840
(He can't breathe.)

1385
00:55:10,840 --> 00:55:12,310
What are we supposed to do?

1386
00:55:12,310 --> 00:55:14,180
This atmosphere is...

1387
00:55:15,120 --> 00:55:16,870
What is this?

1388
00:55:16,870 --> 00:55:18,050
(Wailing)

1389
00:55:18,850 --> 00:55:21,710
- I can't believe this.
 -  I can't look at you in the eyes.

1390
00:55:21,710 --> 00:55:22,770
I know.

1391
00:55:22,770 --> 00:55:25,740
What are we doing? What is this supposed to be?

1392
00:55:25,740 --> 00:55:27,270
What do you want us to do?

1393
00:55:27,270 --> 00:55:29,570
(They're suffocating in the silence.)

1394
00:55:29,570 --> 00:55:31,650
I'll just tell you what I wrote, then.

1395
00:55:32,280 --> 00:55:33,460
Did you write to me?

1396
00:55:33,460 --> 00:55:34,720
I did.

1397
00:55:34,720 --> 00:55:36,950
- I wrote what I was grateful about.
 -  What is it?

1398
00:55:38,320 --> 00:55:40,140
I'm truly grateful to you...

1399
00:55:40,140 --> 00:55:41,270
(I'm truly grateful to you...)

1400
00:55:41,270 --> 00:55:43,320
(Sighing)

1401
00:55:44,820 --> 00:55:45,910
I thought...

1402
00:55:45,910 --> 00:55:47,220
(He's laughing already.)

1403
00:55:49,150 --> 00:55:50,580
It actually occurred to me many times.

1404
00:55:51,520 --> 00:55:56,110
I always questioned whether this was really my place to be.

1405
00:55:56,110 --> 00:55:57,410
(Is this my place to be?)

1406
00:55:57,410 --> 00:55:59,020
I was absorbed in it.

1407
00:55:59,780 --> 00:56:02,250
It's been six years now.

1408
00:56:03,080 --> 00:56:08,310
But in the beginning, I couldn't mingle with the other members.

1409
00:56:08,310 --> 00:56:10,820
(She couldn't open up to the members.)

1410
00:56:10,820 --> 00:56:13,040
I felt bad during that time.

1411
00:56:13,040 --> 00:56:14,270
(I felt sorry at the time.)

1412
00:56:14,270 --> 00:56:15,770
I cried a lot...

1413
00:56:15,770 --> 00:56:18,170
(I cried a lot.)

1414
00:56:18,170 --> 00:56:20,770
And I had a hard time, so I told you that I wanted to quit.

1415
00:56:20,770 --> 00:56:22,740
(I cried a lot and I wanted to quit.)

1416
00:56:22,740 --> 00:56:23,850
- You told me.
 -  I did.

1417
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,040
Whenever I said that...

1418
00:56:26,040 --> 00:56:29,770
(Whenever I said that...)

1419
00:56:29,770 --> 00:56:32,780
You held on to me.

1420
00:56:33,420 --> 00:56:34,840
I'm so thankful...

1421
00:56:34,840 --> 00:56:36,970
(I'm thankful.)

1422
00:56:36,970 --> 00:56:38,110
You listened to me.

1423
00:56:38,110 --> 00:56:40,330
(I'm so thankful that you listened to me.)

1424
00:56:40,330 --> 00:56:43,510
- That's what I wrote.
 -  You're thankful I listened to you.

1425
00:56:43,510 --> 00:56:44,640
I'm thankful about that...

1426
00:56:44,640 --> 00:56:45,710
(Kwang Soo quietly listens to Ji Hyo.)

1427
00:56:45,710 --> 00:56:48,480
And I'm also thankful that you continued to treat me the same.

1428
00:56:49,120 --> 00:56:50,270
That's just...

1429
00:56:50,270 --> 00:56:51,640
(I'm thankful that you treated me the same.)

1430
00:56:51,640 --> 00:56:52,780
How I felt.

1431
00:56:54,280 --> 00:57:01,700
(He is an actor as well, so he could understand her deeply.)

1432
00:57:01,700 --> 00:57:03,180
I did.

1433
00:57:05,580 --> 00:57:07,890
I guess they have a lot to talk to each other.

1434
00:57:07,890 --> 00:57:09,370
(She tries to change the subject.)

1435
00:57:09,370 --> 00:57:10,640
I got something in my eyes.

1436
00:57:10,640 --> 00:57:13,310
- What are you doing?
 -  What am I doing?

1437
00:57:13,310 --> 00:57:16,980
- What are you doing, suddenly?
 -  I got something in my eyes.

1438
00:57:18,550 --> 00:57:22,570
What am I doing here?

1439
00:57:22,570 --> 00:57:24,620
We should be ripping off name tags.

1440
00:57:26,350 --> 00:57:29,780
I wrote what I feel sorry about.

1441
00:57:32,050 --> 00:57:33,540
What makes you feel sorry?

1442
00:57:33,540 --> 00:57:34,880
I...

1443
00:57:37,550 --> 00:57:42,220
I think I act rudely towards you too often.

1444
00:57:43,250 --> 00:57:47,850
We've spent several years together. I know the things that you dislike,

1445
00:57:48,720 --> 00:57:52,350
and I know that I may hurt your feeling if I act in certain ways.

1446
00:57:53,880 --> 00:57:57,820
But I don't how I must act for the best result.

1447
00:57:58,220 --> 00:58:04,450
I want to do well so I do my best, and try hard. But in the end,

1448
00:58:05,580 --> 00:58:07,710
I'm not just saying...

1449
00:58:07,710 --> 00:58:10,610
(I might have hurt Ji Hyo.)

1450
00:58:10,610 --> 00:58:12,650
I am so sorry. But if I say sorry,

1451
00:58:13,150 --> 00:58:17,850
then I shouldn't act like that again. It's really difficult.

1452
00:58:19,150 --> 00:58:20,320
I know.

1453
00:58:22,850 --> 00:58:27,070
Don't worry. I'm fine. Actually, I can't remember.

1454
00:58:27,070 --> 00:58:28,710
What a relief. Because I may keep doing what I was doing.

1455
00:58:28,710 --> 00:58:30,520
Yes, keep behaving like that.

1456
00:58:31,250 --> 00:58:36,080
I think that's better for us. More than talking like this.

1457
00:58:37,920 --> 00:58:39,820
More than talking like this.

1458
00:58:39,820 --> 00:58:41,740
- Oh my.
 -  This is crazy.

1459
00:58:41,740 --> 00:58:44,780
They must have a lot to talk about.

1460
00:58:45,750 --> 00:58:47,340
(How are Jae Seok and Jong Kook in the white room doing?)

1461
00:58:47,340 --> 00:58:51,840
I'm really grateful to you for thinking about me like that.

1462
00:58:51,840 --> 00:58:57,920
To be honest, in the team,

1463
00:58:58,250 --> 00:59:00,970
- I usually stand as an opponent.
 -  Right.

1464
00:59:00,970 --> 00:59:03,110
That's not an easy job for me.

1465
00:59:03,110 --> 00:59:06,210
- Because you're doing it alone.
 -  Yes. And at the same time,

1466
00:59:06,210 --> 00:59:13,210
I have to stand against you, out of all the others. It's not easy.

1467
00:59:13,210 --> 00:59:16,370
- I see.
 -  And things were like that before.

1468
00:59:16,370 --> 00:59:20,510
I did something to you, and it became really controversial.

1469
00:59:20,510 --> 00:59:24,370
I try to forget the burden. I don't have any options.

1470
00:59:24,370 --> 00:59:27,780
- Because it's my job.
 -  It is.

1471
00:59:28,150 --> 00:59:32,740
So I try not to think about that these days.

1472
00:59:32,740 --> 00:59:35,570
I used to say that...

1473
00:59:35,570 --> 00:59:38,080
I can't do anything if people blame me.

1474
00:59:38,720 --> 00:59:40,770
- Because it's my role.
 -  You're right.

1475
00:59:40,770 --> 00:59:43,580
- As long as we're fine about it.
 -  Right.

1476
00:59:44,250 --> 00:59:49,140
Anyway, because it's my job, I keep on acting that way. As I did before.

1477
00:59:49,140 --> 00:59:53,440
- So no matter how much...
 -  You must act like that to anyone.

1478
00:59:53,440 --> 00:59:58,340
That will put us in different situations each time.

1479
00:59:58,340 --> 01:00:01,370
Every member in Running Man is really important.

1480
01:00:01,370 --> 01:00:07,710
And everyone has to do their best in their role for Running Man.

1481
01:00:07,710 --> 01:00:14,880
I must take care of the things that I didn't know until you told me.

1482
01:00:15,220 --> 01:00:18,460
- Jong Kook.
 -  You just keep yourself healthy.

1483
01:00:18,460 --> 01:00:21,710
- You need to keep your health, too.
 -  Of course. Both of us need to.

1484
01:00:21,710 --> 01:00:26,640
I've worked in other entertainment shows, but I think...

1485
01:00:26,640 --> 01:00:30,240
we've spent many years together, and we have the best teamwork.

1486
01:00:30,240 --> 01:00:31,640
Right, of course.

1487
01:00:31,640 --> 01:00:35,580
So if we keep ourselves in good shape,

1488
01:00:35,950 --> 01:00:38,380
- we will be able to keep rolling.
 -  Let's do it.

1489
01:00:38,780 --> 01:00:40,080
That's it.

1490
01:00:40,920 --> 01:00:43,390
- That's right.
 -  Okay. We're done.

1491
01:00:43,390 --> 01:00:44,640
(They feel embarrassed after all the talk.)

1492
01:00:44,640 --> 01:00:47,070
- Okay. We're all set.
 -  Okay.

1493
01:00:47,070 --> 01:00:49,310
- Okay. Keep treating me like that.
 -  I will.

1494
01:00:49,310 --> 01:00:52,330
- Keep it on.
 -  What is it?

1495
01:00:52,330 --> 01:00:56,340
- Okay. Let's go.
 -  Let's go.

1496
01:00:56,340 --> 01:00:57,580
Let's go, Jae Seok.

1497
01:00:58,080 --> 01:01:00,320
All right. We're done.

1498
01:01:01,220 --> 01:01:03,650
(Who's visiting Seok Jin's food stand?)

1499
01:01:06,620 --> 01:01:09,080
(Haha is the one.)

1500
01:01:12,020 --> 01:01:13,610
- Oh my.
 -  My goodness.

1501
01:01:13,610 --> 01:01:15,800
Okay. Take a seat.

1502
01:01:15,800 --> 01:01:18,580
- Nice to see you here, Seok Jin.
 -  Yes. Help yourself.

1503
01:01:19,120 --> 01:01:23,820
- Isn't it the first time?
 -  For us to sit by ourselves.

1504
01:01:24,380 --> 01:01:26,810
- Cheers.
 -  Cheers.

1505
01:01:26,810 --> 01:01:30,220
(It's first time for them to drink together just by themselves.)

1506
01:01:31,250 --> 01:01:33,080
Have I upset you in any way?

1507
01:01:33,980 --> 01:01:35,440
You haven't upset me.

1508
01:01:35,440 --> 01:01:38,850
(How should I put this?)

1509
01:01:39,180 --> 01:01:43,770
- I should apologise.
 -  What are you talking about?

1510
01:01:43,770 --> 01:01:47,640
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

1511
01:01:47,640 --> 01:01:49,250
Oh my.

1512
01:01:50,650 --> 01:01:52,480
For the first few years,

1513
01:01:54,220 --> 01:01:58,020
I kept asking myself...

1514
01:01:59,020 --> 01:02:02,750
why I am doing this every week.

1515
01:02:03,250 --> 01:02:06,750
- But I didn't feel like to quit.
 -  I see.

1516
01:02:07,080 --> 01:02:12,320
Because the style of the show was far too different from others.

1517
01:02:12,780 --> 01:02:18,470
I used to say that it took several years to get used to snap backs.

1518
01:02:18,470 --> 01:02:22,320
Just like that, it took several years to get used to the show.

1519
01:02:22,780 --> 01:02:27,110
I didn't think I fit in well in the team.

1520
01:02:27,110 --> 01:02:29,460
- Did you think that way?
 -  I did.

1521
01:02:29,460 --> 01:02:36,250
I talked to the producer several times about quitting.

1522
01:02:36,250 --> 01:02:41,210
Haha. The thing that I want to tell you is that...

1523
01:02:41,210 --> 01:02:45,510
everyone can be like that. Some may not fit in the show.

1524
01:02:45,510 --> 01:02:47,620
But my fault is...

1525
01:02:49,520 --> 01:02:53,820
that I blamed you guys for it at that time.

1526
01:02:54,280 --> 01:02:57,980
Whatever you said, I was easily offended.

1527
01:02:58,620 --> 01:03:02,610
I just realised that with such act and attitude,

1528
01:03:02,610 --> 01:03:07,220
I couldn't be a comfortable friend or a colleague to you.

1529
01:03:07,720 --> 01:03:10,540
It took a long time for me to realise.

1530
01:03:10,540 --> 01:03:14,590
Then I asked myself, "What should I do?"

1531
01:03:14,590 --> 01:03:17,950
So I started accepting everything.

1532
01:03:17,950 --> 01:03:19,700
(I accepted everything.)

1533
01:03:19,700 --> 01:03:22,950
I realised that I shouldn't feel offended.

1534
01:03:23,750 --> 01:03:29,470
So one day, I started off a race, smiling...

1535
01:03:29,470 --> 01:03:34,080
- We all applauded.
 -  That made me feel comfortable.

1536
01:03:36,450 --> 01:03:39,250
- About that...
 -  I am sorry. I am.

1537
01:03:41,880 --> 01:03:43,710
(Who will be the second guest for Jae Seok?)

1538
01:03:43,710 --> 01:03:46,180
- Hey, Gary.
 -  Yes, Jae Seok.

1539
01:03:46,920 --> 01:03:48,950
Do we need to keep the side open?

1540
01:03:50,380 --> 01:03:54,170
- Hey, Gary. Why are you here?
 -  I was asked to come in.

1541
01:03:54,170 --> 01:03:55,770
- Really?
 -  Yes.

1542
01:03:55,770 --> 01:03:58,650
- I am here, so let me tell you...
 -  All right.

1543
01:03:59,020 --> 01:04:02,950
- My concern is...
 -  Okay.

1544
01:04:02,950 --> 01:04:08,110
My concern as an entertainer is growing bigger these days.

1545
01:04:08,110 --> 01:04:09,910
Jong Kook talked with me about that, too.

1546
01:04:09,910 --> 01:04:11,950
Okay. So...

1547
01:04:13,080 --> 01:04:17,770
Personally, I kept thinking that this might be the end.

1548
01:04:17,770 --> 01:04:20,720
Then I shake my head and cheer myself again.

1549
01:04:21,750 --> 01:04:26,760
But I am afraid that I might lose everything.

1550
01:04:26,760 --> 01:04:28,280
When I try to work on music seriously,

1551
01:04:30,220 --> 01:04:32,580
I often feel that I'm not serious about music.

1552
01:04:33,050 --> 01:04:38,220
I can't concentrate when I didn't make any progress in composing.

1553
01:04:38,720 --> 01:04:44,160
So such things concerned me heavily.

1554
01:04:44,160 --> 01:04:47,480
(Those things concerned me.)

1555
01:04:48,280 --> 01:04:50,920
What burdens me is the question,

1556
01:04:51,620 --> 01:04:53,820
"So, what should I do now?"

1557
01:04:54,450 --> 01:04:59,780
Honestly, I thought I had to quit. It was the best for this show.

1558
01:05:01,950 --> 01:05:05,140
I thought I had to quit...

1559
01:05:05,140 --> 01:05:08,520
for Running Man. Honestly.

1560
01:05:09,450 --> 01:05:14,980
I think everyone including myself will have such concerns.

1561
01:05:16,080 --> 01:05:18,370
We are trying to change ourselves.

1562
01:05:18,370 --> 01:05:21,940
You know, we all used to play in a playground when we were young.

1563
01:05:21,940 --> 01:05:25,570
But as we get older,

1564
01:05:25,570 --> 01:05:30,150
we can't play in the same place forever.

1565
01:05:30,150 --> 01:05:33,910
We won't have much fun playing with the same rides over and over.

1566
01:05:33,910 --> 01:05:40,230
To find different sides of us, we shouldn't do the same things.

1567
01:05:40,230 --> 01:05:43,350
For that, staff members are working hard.

1568
01:05:43,350 --> 01:05:47,270
We don't have any other way but to do our best.

1569
01:05:47,270 --> 01:05:51,140
- I am thinking hard...
 -  Of course.

1570
01:05:51,140 --> 01:05:54,410
- about what I can do for this show.
 -  Of course, I know.

1571
01:05:54,410 --> 01:05:56,740
Staff members are working hard, too.

1572
01:05:56,740 --> 01:05:58,640
That's what we must do for Running Man.

1573
01:05:58,640 --> 01:06:03,640
Staff members are looking for new environments that we can play in.

1574
01:06:03,640 --> 01:06:07,310
That's their concern, and that's what we must do for the show.

1575
01:06:07,310 --> 01:06:09,590
- I will do my best.
 -  Of course.

1576
01:06:09,590 --> 01:06:12,310
- Hey, Gary.
 -  All right.

1577
01:06:12,310 --> 01:06:14,240
(Cheer up, Gary.)

1578
01:06:14,240 --> 01:06:17,740
- Let's go.
 -  All right. That's so simple.

1579
01:06:17,740 --> 01:06:21,050
- It is simple.
 -  It's not difficult at all.

1580
01:06:22,050 --> 01:06:24,380
Oh. come in.

1581
01:06:24,820 --> 01:06:26,510
Take a sit.

1582
01:06:26,510 --> 01:06:28,420
We were having a sincere conversation.

1583
01:06:29,150 --> 01:06:33,740
I am in the middle. Especially, regarding age.

1584
01:06:33,740 --> 01:06:34,930
Yes, you are.

1585
01:06:34,930 --> 01:06:38,340
And Kwang Soo had some difficult times, too.

1586
01:06:38,340 --> 01:06:40,740
- So we talked to each other often.
 -  Did you?

1587
01:06:40,740 --> 01:06:43,630
- He found things difficult, too.
 -  I talked about it with Haha a lot.

1588
01:06:43,630 --> 01:06:46,920
So we cheered up each other and one day,

1589
01:06:47,280 --> 01:06:51,250
Kwang Soo began showing his presence and the show went well.

1590
01:06:51,250 --> 01:06:52,960
I know this is awkward.

1591
01:06:52,960 --> 01:06:56,540
But I want to say I'm really thankful to you, Kwang Soo.

1592
01:06:56,540 --> 01:06:59,650
And you helped me a lot when I had to be funny.

1593
01:07:00,020 --> 01:07:03,330
Seeing you working really hard, I was also motivated a lot.

1594
01:07:03,330 --> 01:07:06,270
Kwang Soo is an actor. So I'm sure it was not easy...

1595
01:07:06,270 --> 01:07:08,250
for him to give up on his image as an actor.

1596
01:07:08,780 --> 01:07:12,640
So I think you should rather be an entertainer than an actor.

1597
01:07:12,640 --> 01:07:14,620
(Do not waste your talent as an entertainer.)

1598
01:07:15,050 --> 01:07:17,270
You're just too funny to remain as an actor.

1599
01:07:17,270 --> 01:07:19,110
Don't try to look handsome.

1600
01:07:19,110 --> 01:07:21,440
That is not what I want.

1601
01:07:21,440 --> 01:07:24,920
- I never tried to look nice.
 -  Okay.

1602
01:07:25,250 --> 01:07:27,450
It's really nice to have this conversation with you.

1603
01:07:29,820 --> 01:07:31,470
(Who is it for the last Apology Service?)

1604
01:07:31,470 --> 01:07:32,880
Hello, you're here.

1605
01:07:33,220 --> 01:07:35,380
It took very long.

1606
01:07:35,750 --> 01:07:37,510
I know, we had a lot to talk about.

1607
01:07:37,510 --> 01:07:41,240
Seok Jin told me his story.

1608
01:07:41,240 --> 01:07:43,400
He told me what happened in his life before.

1609
01:07:43,400 --> 01:07:45,380
(Silent)

1610
01:07:47,750 --> 01:07:49,110
I was going to...

1611
01:07:49,110 --> 01:07:51,500
Gosh, what is this?

1612
01:07:51,500 --> 01:07:53,750
What I want to apologise to you is...

1613
01:07:57,220 --> 01:07:59,550
Oh, my. This isn't what I expected.

1614
01:07:59,880 --> 01:08:02,840
I am sorry that I said you're very ugly.

1615
01:08:02,840 --> 01:08:05,650
- But I know I am ugly too.
 -  Well...

1616
01:08:06,950 --> 01:08:09,060
- What you said is true.
 -  So...

1617
01:08:09,060 --> 01:08:11,200
That is what I thought.

1618
01:08:11,200 --> 01:08:12,530
It is true that I am ugly.

1619
01:08:12,530 --> 01:08:14,170
(They burst into laughter.)

1620
01:08:14,170 --> 01:08:16,640
Haha and I aren't like this!

1621
01:08:16,640 --> 01:08:18,640
My goodness!

1622
01:08:18,640 --> 01:08:20,640
(What is going on between the ugly brothers?)

1623
01:08:20,640 --> 01:08:23,320
Anyway, as we got this chance to talk, I want to tell you this.

1624
01:08:24,880 --> 01:08:29,210
You know I've never appeared on such entertaining shows before.

1625
01:08:29,210 --> 01:08:30,520
And I think...

1626
01:08:31,080 --> 01:08:33,030
you're my role model as an entertainer.

1627
01:08:33,030 --> 01:08:34,650
(You're my role model.)

1628
01:08:35,650 --> 01:08:38,240
(This is so awkward!)

1629
01:08:38,240 --> 01:08:40,480
Okay, I did it!

1630
01:08:41,250 --> 01:08:42,510
I said it.

1631
01:08:42,510 --> 01:08:45,040
So just know that I am grateful to you.

1632
01:08:45,040 --> 01:08:47,320
Okay, I know.

1633
01:08:47,820 --> 01:08:51,170
And you are the best in my life.

1634
01:08:51,170 --> 01:08:53,710
- I love you.
 -  You're my role model.

1635
01:08:53,710 --> 01:08:56,880
Oh, my. You know what?

1636
01:08:57,980 --> 01:08:59,980
I am your fan.

1637
01:09:00,290 --> 01:09:04,420
(Their conversation is full of lines that make you cringe.)

1638
01:09:05,950 --> 01:09:08,410
Gosh, what is this?

1639
01:09:08,410 --> 01:09:10,250
(The Apology Service between the members are over.)

1640
01:09:11,720 --> 01:09:14,850
- Cover your body with this.
 -  No, thanks, my role model.

1641
01:09:16,520 --> 01:09:18,410
- Haha, do you need anything?
 -  I am okay.

1642
01:09:18,410 --> 01:09:20,410
- Then, give that to me.
 -  He is my role model.

1643
01:09:20,410 --> 01:09:21,420
(I'm fine. You can use it.)

1644
01:09:22,290 --> 01:09:23,850
Haha is my role model.

1645
01:09:23,850 --> 01:09:26,280
(They now have strong friendship.)

1646
01:09:26,280 --> 01:09:27,710
You're my idol.

1647
01:09:27,710 --> 01:09:29,310
- Can we wrap this up now?
 -  Yes.

1648
01:09:29,310 --> 01:09:31,070
- So we don't read the letters?
 -  Please...

1649
01:09:31,070 --> 01:09:32,340
burn the letters.

1650
01:09:32,340 --> 01:09:34,040
- Let's burn them.
 -  Okay.

1651
01:09:34,040 --> 01:09:35,610
- Great, let's burn them.
 -  Please.

1652
01:09:35,610 --> 01:09:37,410
- Please burn them.
 -  I think I was out of my mind.

1653
01:09:37,410 --> 01:09:40,290
- I don't want the letters.
 -  I must have been out of my mind.

1654
01:09:40,720 --> 01:09:42,150
(Let's burn the grudges off along with the letters.)

1655
01:09:42,750 --> 01:09:44,440
- Then, let's burn them.
 -  Okay.

1656
01:09:44,440 --> 01:09:46,410
- Let's count to three.
 -  One, two, three.

1657
01:09:46,410 --> 01:09:47,640
- Let's burn them off.
 -  Goodbye.

1658
01:09:47,640 --> 01:09:49,900
- Goodbye.
 -  Bye.

1659
01:09:49,900 --> 01:09:52,720
- Let's not feel sorry any more.
 -  I must have gone out of my mind.

1660
01:09:53,350 --> 01:09:56,870
- And more than 300 guests...
 -  Right.

1661
01:09:56,870 --> 01:09:58,940
appeared on our show.

1662
01:09:58,940 --> 01:10:01,210
- Our guests.
 -  Yes, our guests.

1663
01:10:01,210 --> 01:10:04,540
We were able to meet only a few of them...

1664
01:10:04,540 --> 01:10:05,910
- in this special.
 -  Yes.

1665
01:10:05,910 --> 01:10:07,970
And please join us as our guests...

1666
01:10:07,970 --> 01:10:10,810
if you're willing to.

1667
01:10:10,810 --> 01:10:13,870
We'd like to take this opportunity to say thank you to all the guests.

1668
01:10:13,870 --> 01:10:17,540
And we promise you here that we'll cooperate and...

1669
01:10:17,540 --> 01:10:20,050
work harder to make our guests enjoy the shooting...

1670
01:10:20,050 --> 01:10:23,970
and to make the programme much more enjoyable.

1671
01:10:23,970 --> 01:10:27,010
We will see you next week.

1672
01:10:27,010 --> 01:10:28,470
Shall we hold each other's hand?

1673
01:10:28,470 --> 01:10:30,410
- No.
 -  What are you doing?

1674
01:10:30,410 --> 01:10:31,740
- Gosh.
 -  No way.

1675
01:10:31,740 --> 01:10:33,440
- Let's hold each other's hand.
 -  Thank you, everyone!

1676
01:10:33,440 --> 01:10:35,040
- Hold hands.
 -  My hands are in sweat.

1677
01:10:35,040 --> 01:10:36,570
- Let's hold each other's hand now.
 -  Gosh!

1678
01:10:36,570 --> 01:10:39,470
- My goodness.
 -  Are you living in the 90s?

1679
01:10:39,470 --> 01:10:41,940
- It is very heart-warming.
 -  Why do we have to do this?

1680
01:10:41,940 --> 01:10:44,510
- It is heart-warming.
 -  Thank you, everyone!

1681
01:10:44,510 --> 01:10:46,110
- Thank you!
 -  Thank you!

1682
01:10:46,110 --> 01:10:48,140
- I am sorry, I love you!
 -  I am sorry!

1683
01:10:48,140 --> 01:10:50,210
- Thank you.
 -  Great.

1684
01:10:50,210 --> 01:10:52,830
- It feels good, doesn't it?
 -  Right.

1685
01:10:52,830 --> 01:10:54,110
This makes me feel good.

1686
01:10:54,110 --> 01:10:56,150
- Ji Hyo.
 -  Jae Seok.

1687
01:10:56,150 --> 01:10:58,870
(Next Sunday at 6:25pm)

1688
01:10:58,870 --> 01:11:00,440
(The second episode of "I'm Sorry, I Love You", "Seven Loves")

1689
01:11:00,440 --> 01:11:01,780
(Jae Seok's high school classmate, Lee Seung Joon)

1690
01:11:01,780 --> 01:11:03,370
He's Lee Seung Joon, my high school classmate.

1691
01:11:03,370 --> 01:11:05,410
Jae Seok had a long-term girlfriend.

1692
01:11:05,410 --> 01:11:07,040
She was tall but not pretty.

1693
01:11:07,040 --> 01:11:08,310
You can't do this.

1694
01:11:08,310 --> 01:11:09,740
Seung Joon reveals everything about Jae Seok today.

1695
01:11:09,740 --> 01:11:11,110
He is my role model.

1696
01:11:11,110 --> 01:11:12,940
(Haha's idol, Lee Moon Se)

1697
01:11:12,940 --> 01:11:16,310
I started dreaming to be a singer after listening to his songs.

1698
01:11:16,310 --> 01:11:18,470
Is that your best?

1699
01:11:18,470 --> 01:11:20,640
- Ma'am!
 -  Jong Kook's mother.

1700
01:11:20,640 --> 01:11:22,810
- He is like a daughter.
 -  Daughter?

1701
01:11:22,810 --> 01:11:25,440
- He acts like a daughter at home.
 -  He is a cute boy to his mother.

1702
01:11:25,440 --> 01:11:26,780
See? He's like a daughter.

1703
01:11:26,780 --> 01:11:28,170
(Isn't he?)

1704
01:11:28,170 --> 01:11:29,250
- Hello.
